(3) The power of arrest conferred on a security guard by subsection (2) shall be exercisable— (a) only within, or in the vicinity of, the protected place or protected area at which he is on duty; or (b) at any place other than within, or in the vicinity of, the protected place or protected area at which he is on duty, only after the immediate and continuing pursuit of a person liable to be arrested or detained under this Act who is escaping from the protected area or the vicinity thereof; but not elsewhere or otherwise.
